        <headline>Tornado Warning issued May 30 at 3:59PM EDT until May 30 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm capable of producing a tornado
was located near Buford, or 8 miles northeast of Lancaster, moving
east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated rotation.

IMPACT...Flying debris will be dangerous to those caught without
shelter. Mobile homes will be damaged or destroyed. Damage
to roofs, windows, and vehicles will occur.  Tree damage is
likely.

This dangerous storm will be near...
Buford around 405 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this tornadic thunderstorm include Camp
Creek Fire Station, Taxahaw, Unity Fire Station, Arrowood Estates,
Tradesville, and High Point Fire Station.
</description>
        <instruction>TAKE COVER NOW! If you are outdoors, in a mobile home, or in a
vehicle, move to an interior room or closet on the lowest floor of a
sturdy building immediately.</instruction>
